<para id="fs-idm65557984"><title>Solution</title>
The table can be completed using the following rules:</para>
<list id="fs-idm186359744" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet">
<item>The orbital designation is <emphasis effect="italics">nl</emphasis>, where <emphasis effect="italics">l</emphasis> = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, … is mapped to the letter sequence s, <emphasis effect="italics">p</emphasis>, <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis>, <emphasis effect="italics">f</emphasis>, <emphasis effect="italics">g</emphasis>, <emphasis effect="italics">h</emphasis>, …,</item>
<item>The <emphasis effect="italics">m<sub>l</sub></emphasis> degeneracy is the number of orbitals within an <emphasis effect="italics">l</emphasis> subshell, and so is 2<emphasis effect="italics">l</emphasis> + 1 (there is one <emphasis effect="italics">s</emphasis> orbital, three <emphasis effect="italics">p</emphasis> orbitals, five <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis> orbitals, seven <emphasis effect="italics">f</emphasis> orbitals, and so forth).</item>
<item>The number of radial nodes is equal to <emphasis effect="italics">n –</emphasis> <emphasis effect="italics">l</emphasis> – 1.</item>
</list>
